rComments: She presents the material with a very fresh and enthusiastic demeanor. Genuinely seems to value and deeply consider student input during lectures, which is a point driven home by the importance placed on participation in the course.

Alex was a good instructor. She was very clear about topics discussed in lectures and if you ever had any questions, she was more than willing to answer them. Participation plays a huge role in this course, and there were a lot of not-so-easy assignments. Lectures were long, however, and crammed with material.
Really good professor, she is responsible and enthusiastic, helpful to student. The interaction in the class is very nice.
